<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>POLICE AND CRIME COMMISSIONER FOR CHESHIRE</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:16pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:16pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">Written evidence from </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">John Dwyer</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">, </span><br /><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">Police and Crime Commissioner for Cheshire</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt"> [PCC Progress 05]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I welcome the opportunity to contribute to the Home Affairs Select Committee’s second inquiry into Police and Crime Commissioners.   My submission is based around my own experience as a Police and Crime Commissioner in the areas the Committee has indicated it intends to address.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The effectiveness of Commissioners in reducing crime and delivering an effective police service</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In Cheshire, I have been working closely with the Chief Constable and his senior leadership team to prevent and reduce crime.  Since the introduction of my Police and Crime Plan in April 2013, there have been over 1,000 fewer victims of crime in Cheshire and a 16% reduction in the number of re-offenders.  In September 2013, the Constabulary recorded the lowest volume of crimes for many years and victim satisfaction with the overall service received has increased to 89%, the fourth highest nationally.   </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I have also robustly challenged the Chief Constable in areas where I believe there is a need for improvement.  For instance, I ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> some concern regarding the rate of detections for bur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">glary dwelling offences and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> commissioned HMIC to conduct a formal rev</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">iew of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> burglary investigations.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  As a result of this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the Constabulary introduced more rigour to the process which has positively contributed to the crime and detection figures.</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I have worked with the Constabulary to introduce strategies which tackle issues highlighted within my </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Police and Crime </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Plan, for instance a Mental Health Strategy and a Rural, Heritage and Wildlife Crime Strategy. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Mental Health Strategy will increase the confidence and skills of front line officers in dealing with mental health incidents and use this information with the health service, Mental Health Trusts and local authority partners to develop better pathways to help individuals with mental health needs. For those with acute needs, the focus is on ensuring that they are assessed in appropriate places of safety, particularly when under the influence of alcohol and drugs.  The Rural Crime Strategy will ensure that an effective, efficient and proportionate response is provided to crimes and incidents affecting rural communities and Cheshire’s wildlife and heritage assets.</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In terms of delivering an efficient police service, upon taking up office, I instigated a root and branch review of all aspects of policing in Cheshire.  This review has highlighted </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">areas for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ignificant savings including</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">: re-evaluating building agreements, procurement of uniforms and diesel for the fleet. The review has also led to a new model of policing being designed.  This will focus on local neighbourhood policing with the right capacity and capabilities to meet the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">public’s demand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> supported by lean central capabilities. This emerging model has been costed at £17 million below current costs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will make a significant contribution to the £3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> million savi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ngs required over the next four</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> years</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, whilst protecting frontline policing and enabling some police officer recruitment to take place. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am not complacent and will be seeking further opportunities to increase efficiency and improve services during my term in office.  The transfer of funding to Police and Crime Commissioners to commission services for victims offers a real opportunity for us to put victims at the heart of the criminal justice system and ensure that victims no longer fall through the cracks as has happened in the past.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Through my engagement with the public</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  I have been</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> informed of cases where victims do not appear to have received an appropriate standard of service from the police or criminal justice partners.  As an elected representative of the people of Cheshire, I have challenged the relevant agency in such cases to ensure that lessons are learnt for the future.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The role of the Commissioner in holding the Chief Constable to account</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I have introduced robust mechanisms to ensure that the Chief Constable is effectively held to account on behalf of the people of Cheshire.  Public </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Scrutiny M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eetings are held on a quarterly basis at which the Chief Constable is held to account for performance against the objectives within the Police and Crime Plan and for other aspects of service delivery including financial performance, complaints and human resources.  These meetings are supplemented with monthly private sessions at which I am able </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">scrutinise a broader range of more sensitive operational performance matters.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">7)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I have also appointed a Deputy Commissioner, the former Independent Chairman o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">f the Police Authority, who has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> vast experience in holding the police to account.  The Deputy Commissioner’s portfolio includes in depth scrutiny of human resources, complaints, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">protective services areas of policing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ip sampling of completed complaints files, firearms incidents, and public order incidents</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is undertaken by the Deputy Commissioner</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  I believe that the scrutiny mechanisms which have been introduced provide me with a good understanding of the Constabulary’s performance and have helped contribute to the reductions in crime referred to above.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The role of the Police and Crime Panel in scrutinising the Commissioner </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">8)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I have sought to build a positive and constructive working relationship with the Police and Crime Panel in Cheshire.   I am committed to personally attending Panel meetings so that the Panel can hold me to account for the totality of policing in Cheshire.  The agenda papers for Decision and Scrutiny Meetings are available via my website so the Panel has easy access to the decisions I have made and the information used to hold the Chi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ef Constable to account.  Staff </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">within my office have provided the officers who support the Panel with training so they are able to interpret the performance data which is considered.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">9)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Members of the Panel regularly attend Scrutiny Meetings to observe the Chief Constable being held to account</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, the Members provide written feedback</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Panel </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which gives </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a greater understanding of the challenges faced by the Constabulary and reassurance that I am fulfilling my statutory functions.   I have recently held an informal briefing with the Panel to outline the emerging findings from the root and branch review.  This event was productive and useful for both parties and I have now extended an invitation to the Panel to meet with me informally every six months. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The division of staff and functions and staff between the Commissioner and Chief Constable following the stage 2 transfer</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">10)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Intensive discussion took place with the Chief Constable over the Summer to agree the shape of the Stage 2 transfer in Cheshire.  Our discussions were based around a set of locally agreed key principles for the transfer which included: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ensuring the transfer would enable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the highest quality policing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to be provided </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the people of Cheshire; </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ensuring value for money; </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">standard terms and conditions for staff of both corporation soles to ensure consistency and fairness; and</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">removing bureaucracy and duplication.  </span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">11)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Transfer Scheme which I have submitted meets both the locally agreed transfer principles and those outlined by the Home Secretary. The Stage 2 Transfer Scheme which is currently awaiting the Home Secretary’s determination provides that:  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">All staff shall be transferred to the Chief Constable (except those staff employed in the Office of the Commissioner)</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">All items of equipment and software (and any contracts, agreements, and/or rights and liabilities relating to such items) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will remain with me, but the Chief Constable and his officers and staff will be given unfettered access to these as may be reasonably </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">required for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">policing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">purposes.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  Whilst contracts will be in my name, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Chief Constable shall have the right to take the benefit of any terms of contract</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s via the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> use </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Contracts (Rights of Third Parties) Act 1999</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The estate will remain with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">me but I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> shall make such land and buildings available to be occupied and managed on a day to day basis (including decisions regarding repair and maintenance works and changing or altering operational use) by the Chief Constable for policing purposes as appropriate.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">12)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">As part of the stage 2 transfer process, a revised governance structure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">has been agreed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">with the Chief Constable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which will see </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">decisions being taken at a Joint Management Board.  The new governance arrangements will reduce bureaucracy and duplication</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enable closer joint working between </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">my office </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and the Constabulary</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The role of the Commissioner in budget and precept setting</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">13)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In the current economic climate, a primary consideration for all Police and Crime Commissioners is how to balance the books against a backdrop of reducing financial resources, whilst seeking to maintain and improve services to the public.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">14)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In setting the budget for 2013/14, I had a shortfall of £8m compared to the budget for the previous year.  I proposed to raise the council tax precept by 1.99% to £153</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> for a Band D property</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, for the year 2013/14 and following extensive consultation this was supported by over 80% of the public surveyed. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The public saw t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">his increase of £3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> per annum</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, or 6p per week, as a small price to pay</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to maintain policing services in Cheshire</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> This rise in precept was supported by the Police and Crime Panel and raised £1.2 million to help meet the shortfall.  </span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">15)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am now in the process of considering the budget options for 2014/15.  A revised medium term financial strategy for 2014-18 has recently been approved and, following the root and branch review, I am confident Cheshire is on track to meet the required savings over this period.  Consultation has been taking place with the public and people have been asked whether they would be happy to pay another increase in the policing pa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rt of the council tax. Out of 1084</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> responses to date, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">%</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of people said they would be prepared to pay a similar increase to last year. However, I am aware that people across the board are struggling, as the economy comes out of the recession. Taking all the above into consideration, I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m minded not to increase the council tax precept for policing next year. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The effectiveness of Commissioner’s in promoting local policing priorities</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">16)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A key role of Police and Crime Commissioners is to consult the public on their local priorities for policing to inform the objectives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> contained </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">within the Police and Crime Plan.  During my election campaign, I listened extensively to the views of the public and took this into account when developing my first Police and Crime Plan.  I am committed to ongoing consultation with the public and recently launched a ‘Victim</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s Voice’ campaign to find what victims experience and what they expect from the police, victim support organisations and the criminal justice system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">inform my decisions when I become responsible for commissioning some elements of victims services next year.  My office has also held focus groups with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">many different victims of crime</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to understand their views on policing including: survivors of domestic abuse</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, people with mental health needs and people from the lesbian, gay, bi-sexual and transgender communities and faith groups.</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-35.7pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">17)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are over 1 million people living in Cheshire, and 238,000 of them are under the age of 18.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> I have appointed a Youth Ambassador to represent their views following consultation with young people about what they wanted from this role.  The Youth Ambassador has already gathered the views of over 1000 young people about personal safety, crime and policing and has been working with a myriad of organisations to provide advice and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">understand young people’s views</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The information obtained will be used to influence my Police and Crime Plan and future policing strategies.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#fffefe; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">18)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In order to be accessible to the people of Cheshire, I hold regular surgeries through the County and I have launched the Cheshire Crime Fighter App which enables local people to interact with the Constabulary.    A Crime Prevention Fund has also been launched which allows people to apply for funding to support community projects or initiatives. Since July, I’ve received 40 applications and granted over £58,000. All of the projects aim to improve people’s lives in their local area, by providing services or diversionary activities to reduce crime and anti-social behaviour.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Progress on establishing collaboration agreements with other commissioners, policing organisations and partners</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">19)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Greater collaboration will be essential to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ensure the police service can provide the best possible service to the public.  T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he pace of change on collaboration </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is currently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">too slow</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I believe Commissioners must start driving this agenda now and look beyond regional collaborations which have prevailed in the past.  A good example of looking beyond region</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">al boundaries is the successful, innovative </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">collaboration between Cheshire and Northamptonshire to deliver back office support functions whilst reducing costs.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  In Cheshire, the Constabulary and I are also working with neighbouring forces to explore opportunities for collaboration in respect of both operational policing and back office support functions. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">20)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am a member of the Strategic Police Procurement Board which is working to drive greater collaboration and efficiencies from police procurement practices.  I have also recently met representatives from the Fire &amp; Rescue Service and Ambulance Service to discuss collaboration opportunities between the three services.  Initial discussions have been positive and I am keen that we work together to deliver savings from better joined up working which can be reinvested on the front line.</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Transparency of and reporting by Commissioners to date</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">21)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In order to be accountable to the public, the decisions and performance of Commissioners must be visible and transparent.  I have strived to ensure that I am open and to demonstrate a high level of transparency.  Since taking up office, agenda papers for Decision Meetings and the notes of these meetings have been published on my website, providing details of significant decisions which have been taken.  Registers of interests and expense claims for myself and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Deputy Commissioner are also readily available on the website.   The Office of the Police and Crime Commissioner for Cheshire is able to demonstrate a high level of compliance with the statutory requirements to publish specified information.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>